<paragraph id="680036C15171725F189EFAA9D1B7FAA5" blockId="18.[151,721,1340,1399]" box="[151,443,1374,1399]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
(Pls 1G, 3–5G, 7G; 
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F1979FAA9D1BEFAA5" box="[368,434,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
