<subSubSection id="20A5654A5171725F189EFA51D396F969" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="680036C15171725F189EFA51D396F969" blockId="18.[151,1437,1446,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F189EFA51D11DFA6D" bold="true" box="[151,273,1446,1471]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior katepisternal seta absent (Pl. 1G). First and 2nd tarsomeres of male foreleg dorsodistally extended, with sex-combs: 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F19DEFA3CD26FFA30" box="[471,611,1483,1507]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
with a longitudinal row of 22–29 black, apically blunt teeth along entire length of 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F1904FA18D194F9D4" box="[269,408,1519,1543]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
and a cluster of ca. 6 black, apically sharp teeth distally; 2nd tarsomere with a distal cluster of 3–4 black, apically sharp teeth (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F1A2CF9E5D297F9F9" box="[549,667,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9A,B</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally truncated, with a fringe of 5–7 spines on ventral margin (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F18FFF9C1D16AF99D" box="[246,358,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9C,F</figureCitation>
). Parameres as long as aedeagus, apically curved ventrad and inward, sometimes cruciate, with several minute warts and sensilla scattered on apical to subapical surface (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F1BF9F9ADD479F9A1" box="[1008,1141,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9K–M</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus long, apically strongly curved ventrad and bearing thick hairs like “mop of hair” (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F1BA8F989D42AF945" box="[929,1062,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9K–M</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal capsule wrinkled horizontally in basal 1/4 or less, without apical indentation (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F1B3EF955D381F969" box="[823,909,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9P</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20A5654A5171725918CEF931D330FCEA" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="680036C15171725F18CEF931D2D6F840" blockId="18.[151,1437,1446,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F18CEF931D15EF90D" bold="true" box="[199,338,1734,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F1AB2F930D34AF90C" authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[699,838,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1AB2F930D2C6F90C" box="[699,714,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1AD2F931D34AF90C" box="[731,838,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41F857A85171725F1B46F931D3A7F90D" box="[847,939,1734,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1B46F931D3A7F90D" bold="true" box="[847,939,1734,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD485171725F1C54F930D478F90D" box="[1117,1140,1735,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD485171725F1C8BF930D49AF90D" box="[1154,1174,1735,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head (Pls 1G, 3–5G, 7G): Frontal vitta orange brown. Fronto-orbital pale grayish brown. Ocellar triangle dark brown. Gena pale yellow. Antennal pedicel pale yellow; 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F19F2F8F8D2AAF8F5" box="[507,678,1806,1831]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="flagellomere">st flagellomere</taxonomicName>
yellowish white; arista with 3–4 dorsal and 1 ventral branches and small terminal bifurcation. Supracervical setulae 18¯21 per side; postocular setae 23–25 per side. Clypeus pale yellow. Cibarium with 18–22 medial and 13–15 posterior sensilla per side. Prementum whitish yellow, with 5–6 (1–2 proximal, 2 lateral, and 2 distal) pairs of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15171725E18CEF869D3E5FF2A" blockId="18.[151,1437,1446,2011]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Thorax (Pl. 1G): Postpronotal lobe pale grayish brown, dark brown on anterior margin. Mesonotum yellowish brown, with 3 dark brown, longitudinal stripes; medial stripe anteriorly indistinct, caudally broadened; outer stripes interrupted at transverse suture, sometimes very indistinct. Scutellum yellowish brown, laterally brown. Notopleuron pale grayish brown. Thoracic pleura pale yellow to whitish yellow. Acrostichal setulae in ca. 6 irregular rows. Mid katepisternal seta indistinguishable from those below it.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15170725E18CEFEF2D0D6FE92" blockId="19.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">
Legs (Pl. 1G, 
<figureCitation id="F0842A445170725E196DFEF3D1D5FECE" box="[356,473,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">Fig. 9A,B</figureCitation>
): Apical seta present only on mid-tibia. Midleg 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425170725E1C0EFEF3D498FECE" box="[1031,1172,260,284]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
subproximally without spine.
</paragraph>
