<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35170725E1910F8E5D21CF8FA" bold="true" box="[281,528,1810,1832]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">Lordiphosa anthophilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41F857A85170725E1A1FF8E5D26BF8F5" box="[534,615,1810,1831]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(A, B: paratype #05609; C −M: holotype #05610; N −P: paratype #05606).
</emphasis>
A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425170725E1CB1F8C6D4F4F895" box="[1208,1272,1841,1863]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="and">st and</taxonomicName>
2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="680036C15177725918CEFF60D504FF07" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">Abdomen (Pl. 1E): Tergites nearly entirely black, sometimes anteriorly yellow to yellowish brown, somewhat glossy; tergite II entirely and III anterolaterally yellow to yellowish brown; female tergite VII yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15177725918CEFF28D343FE7F" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A44517772591997FF28D226FF2A" box="[414,554,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">Fig. 9C–M</figureCitation>
): Epandrium yellowish brown, nearly entirely pubescent, caudodorsally triangularly notched, with ca. 24 long setae per side. Cercus yellowish brown, with ca. 19 long setae. Surstylus with a row of 15–16 prensisetae on caudal margin and 36–44 recurved setae on ventral portion of inner surface. Tenth sternite pale brown, moderately sclerotized, flat, medially not concaved. Gonopods rectangular in lateral view, dorsoapically without process, but dorsoproximally with small, claw-like projection. Aedeagus basally membranous, submedially to basally sheathed with gonopods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15177725918CEFE40D239FDEF" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445177725919B8FE40D23AFE02" box="[433,566,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">Fig. 9N–O</figureCitation>
): Tergite VIII yellowish brown. Epiproct and hypoproct grayish brown. Oviscapt valve apicodorsally concave in lateral view, apically with 9̄10 and 8̄9 ovisensilla on dorsal and ventral margins, respectively, laterally with ca. 76 minute ovisensilla. Spermathecal capsule slightly broader than long; introvert about 3/4 height of capsule.
</paragraph>
